the latter case\nhowever, significant information about the slope of $w(z)$ at high redshifts is\nlost. Finally, we propose a new family of parametrizations (nCPL) $w(z)=w_0+w_a\n(\\frac{z}{1+z})^n$ which generalizes the CPL and interpolates between thawing\nand freezing parametrizations as the parameter $n$ increases to values larger\nthan 1.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Mar 2016 17:25:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2016 09:35:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-11"}
