{"id":"1603.02453","submitter":"Yao-Gen Shu","authors":"Yong-Shun Song, Yao-Gen Shu, Xin Zhou, Zhong-Can Ou-Yang, Ming Li","title":"Proofreading of DNA Polymerase: a new kinetic model with higher-order\n  terminal effects","comments":"11 figures","journal-ref":"J. Phys.: Condens. Matter 29 (2017) 025101","doi":"10.1088/0953-8984/29/2/025101","report-no":null,"categories":"q-bio.SC cond-mat.soft","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The fidelity of DNA replication by DNA polymerase (DNAP) has long been an\nimportant issue in biology. While numerous experiments have revealed details of\nthe molecular structure and working mechanism of DNAP which consists of both a\npolymerase site and an exonuclease (proofreading) site, there were quite few\ntheoretical studies on the fidelity issue. The first model which explicitly\nconsidered both sites was proposed in 1970s' and the basic idea was widely\naccepted by later models. However, all these models did not systematically and\nrigorously investigate the dominant factor on DNAP fidelity, i.e, the\nhigher-order terminal effects through which the polymerization pathway and the\nproofreading pathway coordinate to achieve high fidelity. In this paper, we\npropose a new and comprehensive kinetic model of DNAP based on some recent\nexperimental observations, which includes previous models as special cases. We\npresent a rigorous and unified treatment of the corresponding steady-state\nkinetic equations of any-order terminal effects, and derive analytical\nexpressions for fidelity in terms of kinetic parameters under bio-relevant\nconditions. These expressions offer new insights on how the the higher-order\nterminal effects contribute substantially to the fidelity in an order-by-order\nway, and also show that the polymerization-and-proofreading mechanism is\ndominated only by very few key parameters. We then apply these results to\ncalculate the fidelity of some real DNAPs, which are in good agreements with\nprevious intuitive estimates given by experimentalists.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Mar 2016 10:06:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 7 May 2016 13:00:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-29"}
